		},
		{
			"id": 1,
			"parent": 6,
			"text": "In T lymphocytes , the calcium/calmodulin-dependent serine/threonine phosphatase , calcineurin , plays a pivotal role",
			"relation": "BACKGROUND",
			"tag": "Background"
		},
		{
			"id": 2,
			"parent": 1,
			"text": "in transducing membrane-associated signals to the nucleus . <S>",
			"relation": "TEMPORAL",
			"tag": "Background"
		},
		{
			"id": 3,
			"parent": 1,
			"text": "One of the putative targets of calcineurin is the pre-existing , cytosolic component of the nuclear factor of activated T cells ( NFATp ; also referred to as NFAT1 ) , which is one of several transcription factors required for the expression of interleukin 2 . <S>",
			"relation": "ELABORATION",
			"tag": "Background"
		},
		{
			"id": 4,
			"parent": 1,
			"text": "Inhibition of calcineurin by the immunosuppressive drugs cyclosporin A and FK506 prevents dephosphorylation of NFATp and its translocation to the nucleus . <S>",
			"relation": "ADDITION",
			"tag": "Background"
		},
		{
			"id": 5,
			"parent": 4,
			"text": "However , a physical interaction between calcineurin and NFATp has not been demonstrated . <S>",
			"relation": "COMPARISON",
			"tag": "Background"
		},
		{
			"id": 6,
			"parent": 0,
			"text": "Here we demonstrate the binding of NFATp from lysates of T cells to immobilized calcineurin . <S>",
			"relation": "ROOT",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 7,
			"parent": 6,
			"text": "Stimulation of T cells with calcium ionophore induced a shift in the molecular weight of NFATp that is due to its dephosphorylation . <S>",
			"relation": "ELABORATION",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 8,
			"parent": 7,
			"text": "This dephosphorylation was inhibited by treatment of T cells with cyclosporin A or FK506 prior to stimulation . <S>",
			"relation": "ADDITION",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 9,
			"parent": 7,
			"text": "Of note , both the phosphorylated and the dephosphorylated form of NFATp bound to calcineurin . <S>",
			"relation": "ADDITION",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 10,
			"parent": 7,
			"text": "Furthermore , the binding of both forms of NFATp to calcineurin was inhibited by pretreatment of calcineurin with a complex of FK506 and its ligand FKBP12 . <S>",
			"relation": "ADDITION",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 11,
			"parent": 12,
			"text": "Taken together",
			"relation": "CAUSE-RESULT",
			"tag": "Conclusion"
		},
		{
			"id": 12,
			"parent": 6,
			"text": "these data strongly suggest a direct interaction of calcineurin with NFATp and that this interaction does not depend upon the phosphorylation sites of NFATp affected by activation . <S>",
			"relation": "CONCLUSION",
			"tag": "Conclusion"
		}
	]
}